// Figma file u4NLOVKuXUTKULhSn0sAJQ, region y2239.6-2846.8 (node group "1:15778", the
// giant content group, direct children — no wrapping "Programs section" group and no
// eyebrow/H2 exists for this region: get_metadata found no text nodes between
// HowItWorks' own chevron (1:16816, bottom y2086.17) and the first card's own top
// (y2239.6-2239.9) — the stack starts directly, unlike Hero/HowItWorks which both have
// a SectionHeading).
//
// FOUR program cards (O1-O4) OVERLAP HORIZONTALLY like a fan of folders, all sharing the
// same top y (2239.6-2239.9, 0.3px jitter) and the same height (606.86-607.13px, same
// jitter) — a single row, NOT the bottom-aligned "waterfall" of differing heights used by
// HowItWorks/Pillars. Card frames + their REAL (unclipped) border/fill vector, downloaded
// as raw SVG per card (get_design_context flattens these to <img>, so only
// download_assets exposes the actual path + stroke color):
//   O1 (frontmost, fully visible): frame 1:16449 (x122.47, incl. decorative spark below),
//     card border/fill 1:16451 x190.15 w572.54 stroke="#F37D2C" (orange)
//   O2: frame 1:16405 x639.68, border 1:16447 w533.12 stroke="#1E1E3C" (navy), OPEN path
//     (left/bottom edges omitted in the source — already hidden behind O1, never drawn)
//   O3: frame 1:15781 x1058.18, border 1:15817 — reports w659.82 on the GROUP but the
//     border/fill vector's OWN width is only 468.97 (x1058.18-1527.15): O3's real card
//     stops there, which is why O4 peeks out to its own right past that point. stroke
//     navy, open path.
//   O4: frame 1:15820 x1412.28, border 1:15826 w305.72, stroke navy, open path.
// Z-order (front-to-back) O1 > O2 > O3 > O4, evidenced by the border paths themselves
// (the source cards are all fill="none", so fill stacking proves nothing — an earlier
// revision of this comment wrongly claimed it did): every rear card's outline is an OPEN
// path omitting exactly the edges hidden behind its front neighbor. O2 (1:16447,
// `M0 1H418.5L437.57 88.96H533.12V607.86H111.93`) omits its left edge and the bottom run
// x<111.93 (hidden behind O1, which overlaps to x123); O3 (1:15817) omits left + bottom
// x<114.62 (= O2's overlap exactly); O4 (1:15826) omits left + bottom x<113.74 (≈ O3's
// 114.87px overlap); O1 (1:16451) alone is a complete closed outline (`...Z`) — nothing
// sits in front of it.
// Reproduced here with REAL DOM stacking (z-index + negative-margin overlap from the
// measured geometry below) — each card gets its OWN complete rectangle border; the
// occlusion emerges naturally because the front card's opaque `--color-cream` background
// paints over the back card's extra edge, exactly like the source file's own open paths
// (which just never bothered drawing the part that's permanently hidden). Nothing here is
// pre-clipped text.
//
// Row-relative percentages (same technique as Pillars'/HowItWorks' own "gap: X% of the
// design's own row width" — applied to a flex row that fills 100% of `.container`,
// accepting the same built-in row-width/container-width mismatch those precedents already
// ship with). Row span = O1's card-left (190.15) to O4's card-right (1718.0) = 1527.85px:
//   O1 width 572.54/1527.85 = 37.47%      | z-index 4
//   O2 width 533.12/1527.85 = 34.90%      | z-index 3 | margin-left -8.05%  (overlap 123.01px = O1 right 762.69 - O2 left 639.68)
//   O3 width 468.97/1527.85 = 30.69%      | z-index 2 | margin-left -7.50%  (overlap 114.62px = O2 right 1172.8 - O3 left 1058.18)
//   O4 width 305.72/1527.85 = 20.01%      | z-index 1 | margin-left -7.52%  (overlap 114.87px = O3 real-right 1527.15 - O4 left 1412.28)
// (widths sum to 123.07%; minus the three overlaps = 100.00% exactly — the row fills
// `.container` edge to edge with no remainder, unlike the design's own small asymmetric
// insets against its page canvas, an accepted simplification.)
//
// Hover-to-expand width fix (later round): the four DIFFERENT per-card widths/overlaps
// above are what the static Figma collage measures, and are still what renders at rest —
// but once hover could reveal any card's full body copy, keeping each card pinned to its
// own (sometimes much narrower) fan-position width made that card's text wrap into far
// more lines than its neighbors and grow taller than the row. Fixed by collapsing this
// to just two states — WIDE (=O1's 37.47%, unchanged) for whichever card is `.is-active`,
// one shared NARROW (28.345%) for the other three, one shared OVERLAP (7.502% ≈ the same
// 114.62px notch-depth constant already used everywhere else on this page) — see the
// `.card`/`.card.is-active` rules below for the exact derivation. The per-card
// `.card--o1/o2/o3/o4` classes still carry the base z-index stacking (front-to-back at
// rest) and each card's own identity quirks (O1's spark, O4's numeral/label), just not
// sizing anymore.
import SparkFlourishO1 from "../../assets/initiatives/spark-flourish-o1.svg";

// Corner "flag" cut — the top-right corner of EVERY card (O1-O4 alike) is carved AWAY by
// a short diagonal (all four raw border paths: e.g. O1's `H458.921 L477.991 89.5801
// H573.542` — top edge stops 114.62px before the right edge, diagonal 19.07px right over
// a ~88px drop, flat stub to the right edge, then down). The offsets are IDENTICAL across
// all four cards regardless of their differing widths (114.62px cut start / 95.55px cut
// end / 19.07px diagonal span, all from each card's own right edge); only the depth
// jitters (89.58/88.96/86.76/86.96px), unified to the 88.07px mean — HowItWorks' V-tab
// jitter-averaging precedent.
//
// CRITICAL (fix round 1): the notch is a real CUTOUT — a WINDOW through which the card
// behind shows — not a decorative corner drawing. Evidence: (a) the border paths above
// literally exclude the corner region from each card's shape; (b) O2's numeral (1:16438,
// canvas x676.1-762.1) sits entirely INSIDE O1's notch region (x648.07-762.69) and is
// fully visible in the composite; (c) O2's notch left edge (1172.8-114.62 = 1058.18)
// equals O3's card-left EXACTLY — the design aligned the window to frame the next card's
// corner; (d) O4's header fragment ("TED,/H-STAGE CAPITAL", mask window x1418.55-1604.06)
// sits inside O3's notch (x1412.53-1527.15) + the strip beyond O3. An earlier revision
// drew the flag as an opaque cream rect + diagonal, which wrongly COVERED the rear card's
// content (garbling O4's header) and hid O2/O3's numerals.
// Construction: clip-path on .card cuts the notch out of the card's own box (removing
// background AND the CSS border's corner in one stroke — rear card shows through the
// void), and this stroke-only overlay redraws the two border segments the clip leaves
// unpainted (diagonal + flat stub) — the polygon boundary in the .card rule below runs
// along this stroke's OUTER edge (centerline +1px outward) so the 2px stroke survives the
// clip intact. Same two-path split philosophy as HowItWorks' vTab()/Pillars' notch().
// SVG box (see .card-flag CSS): right edge on the border-box's own right edge, top on
// its top edge, width = the card's own --cut percentage + 1px, so the viewBox's x axis
// stretches by exactly the same factor as the %-based clip polygon (they're derived from
// the same design px over the same card width) — svg-local x1 lands on the diagonal
// centerline start, y1 on the top border centerline, and the stub ends at svg x114.62 =
// right border centerline (W-1). y is never scaled (fixed CSS height = viewBox height).
// vector-effect keeps the stroke a true 2px on screen despite the anisotropic x-stretch.
// Hover-to-expand (this task): stroke is `currentColor` instead of a baked-in constant —
// any of the four cards can now be the orange/active one, not just O1, so the color has
// to track `.is-active` dynamically (via `color` on .card-flag below) rather than being
// fixed per card at build time. Single shared markup for all four cards; the two
// differently-named constants this replaced (FLAG_ORANGE/FLAG_NAVY) are gone since
// there's only one variant now.
const CARD_FLAG = `<svg class="card-flag" viewBox="0 0 115.62 90.07" preserveAspectRatio="none" aria-hidden="true" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
    <path d="M1 1 L20.07 88.07 H114.62" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" fill="none" vector-effect="non-scaling-stroke" />
  </svg>`;
