     activation used to be desktop-hover-only with nothing to attach to here (the hover
     script no-ops under 1024) — every card already HAS subtitle/body/status content
     (added a prior task), so this block showed it unconditionally instead of gating on
     `.is-active`. That's still true, but `.is-active` itself is no longer permanently
     frozen on O1 at this width: the scroll-driven activation added below (see the
     script) now toggles it as the user scrolls, same as HowItWorks' own mobile fix —
     this block's job is still just subtitle/body/status visibility, not gating who's
     active. */
  @media (max-width: 1023.98px) {
    .card-subtitle,
    .card-body {
      display: block;
    }
    .card-status {
      display: inline-flex;
