       the right below 1024px, out of line with the numeral/label/body above them,
       and the chips — squeezed into the sliver of width left over — wrapped to one
       per row and read as vertically stacked/centered instead of flowing from the
       left. Root cause: `.card:not(.is-active) .card-title`'s `margin-left:
       var(--cut)` and `.card:not(.is-active) .card-footer`'s `padding-left:
       var(--cut)` (both defined above, desktop-only in intent) exist to shift a
       collapsed desktop card's content clear of the fan-overlap notch — but
       neither rule was ever scoped to desktop, so it kept applying here too, at
       whatever fixed `--cut` this breakpoint sets (114.62px — a lot of a
       ~375-430px phone screen). There's no overlap in this stacked full-width
       layout to compensate for, so both are reset back to the same inset every
       other element in the card already uses. */
    .card:not(.is-active) .card-title {
      margin-left: 2.36rem;
    }
    .card:not(.is-active) .card-footer {
      padding-left: 2.36rem;
    }
    /* Per direct feedback: these used to be flat fixed sizes (the exact desktop-1920
       design px) applied across the ENTIRE <1024px range — fine at tablet widths close
       to 1024, but way oversized on phones (chips especially, at a flat 20px/1.25rem
       plus their own pill padding, read as "too too large" on a ~375-430px screen), and
       inconsistent since only .card-num/.card-title got a further step-down at <640px
       while chips/labels/body never did. Replaced with one continuous `clamp()` per
       role spanning the whole <1024px range instead of a flat value: each ceiling
       matches the exact value that used to apply right at the 1024px boundary (so
       nothing changes at 1024 itself, and desktop — governed by its own separate ≥1024
       rules above, untouched — never sees any of this), scaling down smoothly via vw
       as the viewport narrows, down to a floor chosen for legibility at small phone
       widths (~375px and below, where every one of these floors is what actually
       renders, same "phones get one consistent size, tablets scale" shape as the
       desktop clamps elsewhere in this file). Removed the old separate <640px
       overrides for `.card-num`/`.card-title` entirely — they'd fight this new
       continuous scaling if they stuck around (a fixed value later in the cascade
       would just override the floor these clamps already provide, undoing the fix
       specifically in the phone range this was meant to fix). */
    .card-num {
      font-size: clamp(1.9rem, 5.622vw, 3.5988rem);
    }
    .card-label,
    .card-subtitle,
    .chip {
      font-size: clamp(0.85rem, 1.953vw, 1.25rem);
    }
    .card-title {
      font-size: clamp(1.7rem, 4.97vw, 3.1806rem);
    }
    .card-body {
      font-size: clamp(0.95rem, 1.953vw, 1.25rem);
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 639.98px) {
